  "root_text": {
    "dhp157:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp157:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp157:0.3": "Attavagga ",
    "dhp157:0.4": "Bodhirājakumāravatthu ",
    "dhp157:1": "Attānañce piyaṁ jaññā, ",
    "dhp157:2": "rakkheyya naṁ surakkhitaṁ; ",
    "dhp157:3": "Tiṇṇaṁ aññataraṁ yāmaṁ, ",
    "dhp157:4": "paṭijaggeyya paṇḍito. ",
    "dhp158:0": "Upanandasakyaputtattheravatthu ",
    "dhp158:1": "Attānameva paṭhamaṁ, ",
    "dhp158:2": "patirūpe nivesaye; ",
    "dhp158:3": "Athaññamanusāseyya, ",
    "dhp158:4": "na kilisseyya paṇḍito. ",
    "dhp159:0": "Padhānikatissattheravatthu ",
    "dhp159:1": "Attānañce tathā kayirā, ",
    "dhp159:2": "yathāññamanusāsati; ",
    "dhp159:3": "Sudanto vata dametha, ",
    "dhp159:4": "attā hi kira duddamo. ",
    "dhp160:0": "Kumārakassapamātuttherivatthu ",
    "dhp160:1": "Attā hi attano nātho, ",
    "dhp160:2": "ko hi nātho paro siyā; ",
    "dhp160:3": "Attanā hi sudantena, ",
    "dhp160:4": "nāthaṁ labhati dullabhaṁ. ",
    "dhp161:0": "Mahākālaupāsakavatthu ",
    "dhp161:1": "Attanā hi kataṁ pāpaṁ, ",
    "dhp161:2": "Attajaṁ attasambhavaṁ; ",
    "dhp161:3": "Abhimatthati dummedhaṁ, ",
    "dhp161:4": "Vajiraṁvasmamayaṁ maṇiṁ. ",
    "dhp162:0": "Devadattavatthu ",
    "dhp162:1": "Yassa accantadussilyaṁ, ",
    "dhp162:2": "māluvā sālamivotthataṁ; ",
    "dhp162:3": "Karoti so tathattānaṁ, ",
    "dhp162:4": "yathā naṁ icchatī diso. ",
    "dhp163:0": "Saṅghabhedaparisakkanavatthu ",
    "dhp163:1": "Sukarāni asādhūni, ",
    "dhp163:2": "attano ahitāni ca; ",
    "dhp163:3": "Yaṁ ve hitañca sādhuñca, ",
    "dhp163:4": "taṁ ve paramadukkaraṁ. ",
    "dhp164:0": "Kālattheravatthu ",
    "dhp164:1": "Yo sāsanaṁ arahataṁ, ",
    "dhp164:2": "ariyānaṁ dhammajīvinaṁ; ",
    "dhp164:3": "Paṭikkosati dummedho, ",
    "dhp164:4": "diṭṭhiṁ nissāya pāpikaṁ; ",
    "dhp164:5": "Phalāni kaṭṭhakasseva, ",
    "dhp164:6": "attaghātāya phallati. ",
    "dhp165:0": "Cūḷakālaupāsakavatthu ",
    "dhp165:1": "Attanā hi kataṁ pāpaṁ, ",
    "dhp165:2": "attanā saṅkilissati; ",
    "dhp165:3": "Attanā akataṁ pāpaṁ, ",
    "dhp165:4": "attanāva visujjhati; ",
    "dhp165:5": "Suddhī asuddhi paccattaṁ, ",
    "dhp165:6": "nāñño aññaṁ visodhaye. ",
    "dhp166:0": "Attadatthattheravatthu ",
    "dhp166:1": "Attadatthaṁ paratthena, ",
    "dhp166:2": "bahunāpi na hāpaye; ",
    "dhp166:3": "Attadatthamabhiññāya, ",
    "dhp166:4": "sadatthapasuto siyā. ",
    "dhp166:5": "Attavaggo dvādasamo. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp157:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp157:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 157–166 ",
    "dhp157:0.3": "12. The Self ",
    "dhp157:0.4": "",
    "dhp157:1": "If you knew your self as beloved, ",
    "dhp157:2": "you’d look after it so well. ",
    "dhp157:3": "In one of the night’s three watches, ",
    "dhp157:4": "an astute person would remain alert. ",
    "dhp158:0": "",
    "dhp158:1": "The astute would avoid being corrupted ",
    "dhp158:2": "by first grounding themselves ",
    "dhp158:3": "in what is suitable, ",
    "dhp158:4": "and then instructing others. ",
    "dhp159:0": "",
    "dhp159:1": "If one were to treat oneself ",
    "dhp159:2": "as one instructs another, ",
    "dhp159:3": "the well-tamed indeed would tame: ",
    "dhp159:4": "for the self, it seems, is hard to tame. ",
    "dhp160:0": "",
    "dhp160:1": "One is indeed the lord of oneself, ",
    "dhp160:2": "for who else would be one’s lord? ",
    "dhp160:3": "By means of a well-tamed self, ",
    "dhp160:4": "one gains a lord that’s rare indeed. ",
    "dhp161:0": "",
    "dhp161:1": "For the evil that is done by oneself, ",
    "dhp161:2": "born and produced in oneself, ",
    "dhp161:3": "grinds down a simpleton, ",
    "dhp161:4": "as diamond grinds a lesser gem. ",
    "dhp162:0": "",
    "dhp162:1": "One choked by immorality, ",
    "dhp162:2": "as a sal tree by a creeper, ",
    "dhp162:3": "does to themselves ",
    "dhp162:4": "what a foe only wishes. ",
    "dhp163:0": "",
    "dhp163:1": "It’s easy to do bad things ",
    "dhp163:2": "harmful to oneself, ",
    "dhp163:3": "but good things that are helpful ",
    "dhp163:4": "are the hardest things to do. ",
    "dhp164:0": "",
    "dhp164:1": "On account of wicked views—",
    "dhp164:2": "scorning the guidance ",
    "dhp164:3": "of the perfected ones, ",
    "dhp164:4": "the noble ones living righteously—",
    "dhp164:5": "the idiot begets their own self’s demise, ",
    "dhp164:6": "like the bamboo bearing fruit. ",
    "dhp165:0": "",
    "dhp165:1": "For it is by oneself that evil’s done, ",
    "dhp165:2": "one is corrupted by oneself. ",
    "dhp165:3": "It’s by oneself that evil’s not done, ",
    "dhp165:4": "one is purified by oneself. ",
    "dhp165:5": "Purity and impurity are personal matters, ",
    "dhp165:6": "no one can purify another. ",
    "dhp166:0": "",
    "dhp166:1": "Never neglect what is good for yourself ",
    "dhp166:2": "for the sake of another, however great. ",
    "dhp166:3": "Knowing well what is good for yourself, ",
    "dhp166:4": "be intent upon your heart’s goal. ",
    "dhp166:5": ""
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "dhp161:1": "Attanā hi → attanā va (bj, sya-all, pts1ed, pts2ed) ",
    "dhp161:3": "Abhimatthati → abhimanthati (bj) ",
    "dhp161:4": "Vajiraṁvasmamayaṁ → vajiraṁvamhayaṁ (sya-all); vajiraṁva'mhamayaṁ (pts1ed, pts2ed, mr) ",
    "dhp164:6": "attaghātāya → attaghaññāya (bj, sya-all, pts1ed, pts2ed) ",
    "dhp165:1": "Attanā hi → attanā va (bj, sya-all, pts1ed, pts2ed) ",
    "dhp165:6": "aññaṁ → nāññamañño (bj) "
  },
